Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on wireless-powered sensor networks and their energy management, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed energy management scheme for the WPSN involves controlling the energy transfer efficiency, which is a system and control problem. 
3. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The use of wireless power transfer for sensor networks is an emerging technology, which is discussed in the paper. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The interaction between the components of the WPSN can be viewed as a multiagent system, where each component has its own behavior and goals. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves analyzing the interaction between components of the WPSN and setting up a realistic model, which can be viewed as an information theory problem.
